    <sect3 role="package">
      <title>Introdução a File::chdir</title>

      <para>
        File::chdir provides a more sensible way to change directories.
      </para>

      <para>
        Perl's chdir() has the unfortunate problem of being very, very, very
global. If any part of your program calls chdir() or if any library you use
calls chdir(), it changes the current working directory for the *whole*
program. File::chdir gives you an alternative, $CWD and @CWD.
      </para>

      &lfs113_checked;

